sql:
SELECT name 
FROM companies 
WHERE total_inbound_links > (
  SELECT AVG(total_inbound_links) 
  FROM companies
);

external_knowledge:
- 'prominent marketing firms' refers to companies operating in the 'Marketing' industry;
- 'significant customer count score' means the metric value for 'Customer Count Score' is over 1000;
- 'overall client base' is synonymous with the total number of customers a company has.

- "performance in attracting customers" refers to the customer count score;
- "general performance" refers to the overall score;
- The primary focus is on companies that perform better in customer acquisition first, followed by their general performance ranking.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM company_metrics cm
WHERE CAST(cm.score AS REAL) > (
  SELECT AVG(CAST(score AS REAL))
  FROM company_metrics
);

external_knowledge:
'sailed the stormiest seas of traffic' refers to companies that have been through high traffic conditions;
'the peak of their voyage has surpassed the 500 mark' means their maximum traffic metric value was greater than 500;
'depth of their journey' refers to the detailed metrics obtained for each company.

